  "summary": "Eight valence electrons: two O–H bonding pairs and two lone pairs on oxygen. Four electron domains around O make the electron geometry tetrahedral, but the two lone pairs push the two bonds together into a bent molecule. Because the shape is bent, the two polar O–H bond dipoles do not cancel — water is the archetypal polar molecule, and that net dipole is why it dissolves salts and boils far higher than its mass predicts.",
